   version stable 0.99.81 0.99.80
   require alsa-lib gtk+ madplay
  optional audiofile  --enable-audiofile --disable-audiofile     to play aiff, snd wave, and au files
  optional doxygen    ''                 ''                      for generating documenation
  optional flac       --enable-flac      --disable-flac          to support audio codec
  optional esound     --enable-esd       --disable-esd           to use esd for audio output
  optional jackit     --enable-jack      --disable-jack          for audio server support
  optional libmikmod  --enable-mikmod    --disable-libmikmodtest to play mod, s3m, xm, it, med, 669 files
  optional libsndfile ''                 ''                      to build sndfile input plugin
  optional libvorbis  --enable-oggvorbis --disable-vorbistest    to play oggvorbis files
  category audio/player
 attribute x11
    source http://www.alsaplayer.org/ ftp://ftp.alsa-project.org/pub/people/andy/ alsaplayer-$VERSION.tar.bz2
      vurl http://www.alsaplayer.org/download.php
      info home  http://www.alsaplayer.org/
      info docs  http://www.alsaplayer.org/docs.php
# might only require libmad
      opts --disable-nas
#     opts --disable-nas --enable-gtk2
# gtk2 support not yet complete in alsaplayer 0.99.77
      desc 'PCM player that outputs using ALSA
It is heavily multi-threaded and tries to
excercise the ALSA library and driver quite a bit.
It has some very interesting features unique to Linux/Unix players.
The goal is to create a fully pluggable framework for playback
of all sorts of media with the focus on PCM audio data.

alsaplayer must be on hold or sold to remain installed
until software authors release a new bug fixed version.'
